---
/**
 * Privacy Policy (Datenschutzerklärung).
 *
 * Covers GDPR Arts. 13/14 — categories of data, legal basis, retention,
 * recipients/processors, data subject rights, supervisory authority.
 * Written for B2B buyers of PartnerScope and for Free-Snapshot leads.
 */

import Legal from '../../layouts/Legal.astro';
---
<Legal
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How PartnerScope (EKM Global Consulting GmbH) processes personal data under the GDPR."
  lastUpdated="2026-04-21"
>
  <p>
    This policy explains how EKM Global Consulting GmbH ("PartnerScope", "we") processes personal
    data in connection with the PartnerScope website (partnerscope.eu) and the PartnerScope
    third-party AI risk assessment service. It is written to meet our obligations under the EU
    General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the Austrian Data Protection Act (DSG).
  </p>

  <h2>1. Controller</h2>
  <p>
    EKM Global Consulting GmbH, Vienna, Austria. Contact:
    <a href="mailto:hello@partnerscope.eu">hello@partnerscope.eu</a>. Full statutory disclosure in
    our <a href="/legal/imprint">Imprint</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Categories of data we process</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Category</th><th>Examples</th><th>Source</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Account and contact</td>
        <td>Name, work email, employer, role</td>
        <td>You — via the Free Snapshot form, /get-started, or direct email</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Assessment input</td>
        <td>Vendor domain, questionnaire answers, uploaded documents</td>
        <td>You — during an assessment</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Billing</td>
        <td>Invoice address, VAT ID, payment timestamps</td>
        <td>You and our payment processor (Stripe)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Technical</td>
        <td>IP address, user-agent, request logs, timestamps</td>
        <td>Automatically, when you use the site / API</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Marketing (only if you opt in)</td>
        <td>Email address and campaign tags</td>
        <td>You — via explicit consent</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>3. Purposes and legal basis</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Providing the service</strong> (account creation, running assessments, delivering
      reports) — Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of contract).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Free Snapshot lead magnet</strong> (scoring the snapshot and emailing results) —
      Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR (pre-contractual measures) and Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent for the result
      email).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Billing and accounting</strong> — Art. 6(1)(c) GDPR (legal obligation under
      Austrian tax and accounting law, UGB § 190).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Security and abuse prevention</strong> (request logs, rate limiting, anti-fraud) —
      Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in running a secure service).
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Marketing emails</strong> — Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR (consent). Every marketing email
      includes a one-click unsubscribe link.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Retention</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Free-Snapshot leads: <strong>90 days</strong>, then deleted or anonymised.</li>
    <li>Assessment reports: <strong>validity period</strong> (90 days for Starter, 180 days for Pro) + 12 months of reference retention, then deleted on request.</li>
    <li>Billing records: <strong>7 years</strong> (statutory retention under Austrian BAO § 132).</li>
    <li>Server request logs: <strong>30 days</strong>.</li>
    <li>Marketing list: until you unsubscribe.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Recipients and sub-processors</h2>
  <p>
    We share personal data only with processors that help us deliver the service. Every processor
    is bound by a GDPR-compliant Data Processing Agreement. The current list is public and kept
    up to date at <a href="/legal/sub-processors">/legal/sub-processors</a>. Typical recipients:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Stripe Payments Europe, Ltd. (payment processing)</li>
    <li>Resend Inc. (transactional email)</li>
    <li>Our EU hosting provider (application and database hosting)</li>
    <li>Competent authorities where we are required to disclose by law</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Our primary infrastructure and data stores are hosted in the European Union. Where a
    sub-processor transfers data outside the EEA, we rely on the European Commission's Standard
    Contractual Clauses (Art. 46(2)(c) GDPR) and apply supplementary measures where required.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You have the right to (a) access your data, (b) rectify it, (c) request erasure, (d) request
    restriction, (e) data portability, and (f) object to processing based on legitimate interest.
    Where processing is based on consent, you may withdraw consent at any time without affecting
    the lawfulness of processing before the withdrawal.
  </p>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these rights, email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@partnerscope.eu">privacy@partnerscope.eu</a>. We respond within the
    GDPR statutory period (one month, extendable by two further months for complex cases).
  </p>

  <h2>8. Right to lodge a complaint</h2>
  <p>
    You may file a complaint with the Austrian Data Protection Authority
    (Datenschutzbehörde — dsb.gv.at), or with the supervisory authority of the EU member state
    where you live or work.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Cookies and tracking</h2>
  <p>
    The marketing site uses strictly necessary cookies only and does not set any advertising or
    cross-site tracking cookies. If we add analytics in future (e.g. a privacy-respecting,
    cookieless tool), we will update this policy before rollout.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Automated decision-making</h2>
  <p>
    The PartnerScope scoring is model-assisted: automated checks and scoring produce a draft risk
    profile, but every Pro and Enterprise report is reviewed by a human analyst before delivery.
    Starter reports are delivered without individual analyst review and are explicitly marketed
    as such — they do not produce legal or similarly significant effects on any data subject and
    therefore fall outside Art. 22(1) GDPR.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We update this policy when our processing activities change. Material changes are announced
    by email to registered customers at least 30 days before they take effect.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-note">
    This policy is a first, good-faith draft. Have it reviewed by a qualified Austrian/EU
    data-protection counsel before relying on it in contract negotiations or audits.
  </div>
</Legal>
